                                 <dim unit="leaf">9</dim>
                                 <locus from="72r" to="80v"/> VII(9/fols. 72r-80v).</item>
                           </list>
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">The boards and more than a half of the fols. are
                           missing. 
 Most of the fols. are worn, stained with water.
 Some
                           fols. are misplaced (fols. 4, 5, 6, 7, 10).
 f. 6 is loose.
                              <locus target="#15">15</locus>, 62, 79, 80 are damaged with portions
                           of the text lost.
 Cut carefully amended in <locus target="#19">19</locus>.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="17">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height>105</height>
                              <width>90</width>
                              <dim type="intercolumn"/>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top">30</dim>
                              <dim type="bottom">50</dim>
                              <dim type="right">45</dim>
                              <dim type="left">5</dim>
                              <dim type="intercolumn"/>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>All data are for <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>.</note>
                           <ab type="ruling"/>
                           <ab type="pricking">Pricking and ruling arPrimary pricks are not visible.
                              partly visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling" subtype="pattern"> Ruling pattern:
                              1A-1A/0-0/0-0/C.</ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Ruling pricks are visible (s. <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>, 7r).</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The upper line is written above the ruling. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>18th century (?).</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Numbers and titles of the Psalms; names of the
                           Hebrew letters in Ps. 118; elements of the punctuation signs; caesura
                           sign (fol. 29r).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The quality of the handwriting is
                        changing: from thin, slightly left-sloping, very broadly spaced letters
                        (fols 1r-13v), to somewhat thicker, rounded, left-sloping letters (<locus from="14r" to="80v">14r-80v</locus>).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">Shelfmark <locus target="#46v">46v</locus>
                           - The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the end of the line: e.g., fols. 1r l.15, 23v l.16, 49v l.4, 51r l.3, 62r l.11. 
                           - Corrections written interlineally: e.g. fols. 3v l.8, 6r l.16, 10r l.1. 
                           - Erasures: <locus target="#6r">fol.  6r</locus> l.1 (marked with three lines above), <locus target="#7r">fol.  7r</locus> l.9 (marked with a line of dots placed between two lines), <locus target="#34v">fol.  34v</locus> l.4 (marked with black and red lines). 
                           - Erased line: <locus target="#7r">fol.  7r</locus> l.5. 
                           - Part of the line is taken up on fols. 29r l.10, 31v l.16, 61v l.8, 63v l.2.
                           - Part of the line is taken down on <locus target="#44v">fol.  44v</locus> l. 5. 
                           - Some Psalms are numbered twice, in black and red (fols. 50v, 64v, 65v, 67v, 69v, 71v).
                           - The numbers of some Psalms are alternated in black and red ink: e.g., fols. 1v, 2r, 3r, 7r, 8v, 10v, 13v, 13v, 14r, 14v, 16v, 31r. 
                           - The number of Psalm 130 is repeated on fols. 67v, 69v, 71v. 
                           - Ps. 118 is not numbered.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="false">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Both boards are missing; only small fragments of the
                           original binding have been preserved. 
 Probably two pairs of sewing
                           stations (s. <locus target="#30r">30r</locus>).</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">All quires are reinforced by parchment
                           guards.</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
